h3. *Summary*

Sometimes there are problems in the workflows that are not fixable if not demanding work from the support (e.g. workflow corruption).

h3. Suggestion

Before contacting support, there could be a option to check the workflow's integrity:
* Steps;
* Transitions;
* Incorrect data in the workflow's XML;
* etc.

h3. Summary
When hovering over the reporter of an issue, you can select More > Current issues. However, this option would only return results for JQL {code}assignee = "reporter_name" AND resolution is EMPTY{code} instead of {code}reporter = "reporter_name" AND resolution is EMPTY{code}

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# In issue view, hover over the reporter name. Click on More, then Current Issues.

h3. Expected Results
JQL returns {code}reporter = "reporter_name" AND resolution is EMPTY{code}
h3. Actual Results
{code}assignee = "reporter_name" AND resolution is EMPTY{code}

h3.Workaround
Manually change the field *assignee* to *reporter* in the JQL

